{
  "texts": [
    "In traditional encoding methods, the three classification features are converted to numerical data [0,1,2].",
    "Regarding the algorithm, these three numbers are not equal but are continuous and computable.",
    "This process disregards the mathematical properties contained in the numbers and transmits incorrect information to the algorithm.",
    "Therefore, one-hot encoding is used to convert nominal variables to dummy variables, as shown in Fig. 7.",
    "The fourth step is to define the column names, labels and data."
  ]
}